divs: Sighting DetailsI was on the second to last hole in my golf league (830pm) and was waiting for the group in front of us. I looked up at the clouds as the cloud structures were pretty interesting and noticed what I thought was a plane. As I kept looking at it I began to think it was an interesting looking plane. What was strange was that it was extremely shiny and all silver in color. I could not make out any wings, tail, or trail behind the object. The shape was circular. It was high and moving from west to east. I lost sight of it once it entered a cloud. The sky was clear when I saw it and I was able to see it for about 2 minutes.
